<title>USA: US Airways route cuts aimed at pilots - union.</title>
<headline>US Airways route cuts aimed at pilots - union.</headline>
<dateline>PITTSBURGH 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>The union representing pilots at US Airways Group Inc said Thursday the company's decision to cut unprofitable routes in a restructuring was mainly designed to test the pilots' resolve in contract talks.</p>
<p>The master executive council of the Air Line Pilots Association (ALPA) said in a statement the group was committed to working for a fair and effective contract.</p>
<p>&quot;Although some of (management's) actions may be for legitimate financial reasons, we believe that the primary reason is to test our resolve and influence the negotiations,&quot; the statement said.</p>
<p>US Airways announced Thursday a restructuring that calls for it to eliminate unprofitable routes, consolidate facilities and reduce its fleet.</p>
<p>((-- New York newsdesk, (212) 859-1610))</p>
